Exploratory analysis: Henri 2 grouping

Henri typology

When dealing with the data it becomes apparent that we need to use some criteria for identifying dimensions. These are useful to bear in mind:

-A dimension should have a minimum number of items, otherwise it becomes too unstable and not a reliable measure. Thus, 2 items is too few to measure a dimension. Ideally should be above 3 to get a more precise measure.

-Item 47 on Constitutional amendments poses a problem for the inclusion of Law-initiated (should consider leaving out as suggested in earlier discussions)
